195–1242":"1195–1242","1125–1187":"1125–1187","1132–1200":"1132–1200","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","9 September 1195":"9. září 1195","1217":"1217","30 June 1160":"30. června 1160","1125":"1125","1200":"1200","15 January 1217":"15. ledna 1217","2 februari 1187":"2. února 1187","Heusden, Asten, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Asten, Noord-Brabant, Nizozemsko","Heusden, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Noord-Brabant, Nizozemsko","Salm, Daun, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Salm, Daun, Rheinland-Pfalz, Německo"},"da":{"30 June 1160–15 January 1217":"30. juni 1160–15. januar 1217","1160–1217":"1160–1217","–Female":"Afdød","1195–1242":"1195–1242","1125–1187":"1125–1187","1132–1200":"1132–1200","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","9 September 1195":"9. september 1195","1217":"1217","30 June 1160":"30. juni 1160","1125":"1125","1200":"1200","15 January 1217":"15. januar 1217","2 februari 1187":"2. februar 1187","Heusden, Asten, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Asten, Noord-Brabant, Nederlandene","Heusden, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Noord-Brabant, Nederlandene","Salm, Daun, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Salm, Daun, Rheinland-Pfalz, Tyskland"},"nl":{"30 June 1160–15 January 1217":"30 juni 1160–15 januari 1217","1160–1217":"1160–1217","–Female":"Overleden","1195–1242":"1195–1242","1125–1187":"1125–1187","1132–1200":"1132–1200","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","9 September 1195":"9 september 1195","1217":"1217","30 June 1160":"30 juni 1160","1125":"1125","1200":"1200","15 January 1217":"15 januari 1217","2 februari 1187":"2 februari 1187","Heusden, Asten, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Asten, Noord-Brabant, Nederland","Heusden, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Noord-Brabant, Nederland","Salm, Daun, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Salm, Daun, Rheinland-Pfalz, Duitsland"},"en":{"30 June 1160–15 January 1217":"30 June 1160–15 January 1217","1160–1217":"1160–1217","–Female":"Deceased","1195–1242":"1195–1242","1125–1187":"1125–1187","1132–1200":"1132–1200","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","9 September 1195":"9 September 1195","1217":"1217","30 June 1160":"30 June 1160","1125":"1125","1200":"1200","15 January 1217":"15 January 1217","2 februari 1187":"2 February 1187","Heusden, Asten, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Asten, North Brabant, Netherlands","Heusden, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, North Brabant, Netherlands","Salm, Daun, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Salm, Daun, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"van","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Anh, Thanh, Hung, Minh, Vinh, Dung, Hue, Huong, Lan, Quang, Tan, Thuy, Hong, Chi, Hang, Ho, Pok, Sang, Bai, Chin, Ching, Chu, Chuan, Dong.","Vietnamese (<b>Vạn</b>): from the Chinese surname 萬, see   Wan   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Văn</b>): from the Chinese surnames 文 or 聞, see   Wen   2 and 3, and also 5 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Wan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Hong, Yi, Qi, Qiang, Wai, Yiu, Yuk, Chien-Min, Fang, Hin, Jichun, Li, Man, Chung, Min, Yiping, Pak, Sik, Sung Man.  Vietnamese Tin, Bang, Da, Hien, Hoi, Lan, Minh Quang, Sau, Tich, Tung, Yaping, Yuet.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 萬, which means ‘ten thousand’ literally or ‘very great number’ figuratively: (i) from the personal name of Bi Wan (畢萬), an official in the state of Jin (located in present-day Shanxi province). He was said to be a descendant of Bi Gong Gao (known as Duke of Bi), the 15th son of the virtuous King Wen of Zhou (reined 1152–1056  BC ). Bi Wan was later granted the fiefdom of Wei (魏), which in 403  BC  became the state of Wei (located in present-day Shanxi, Shaanxi, Henan and Hebei provinces). Some of his descendants adopted Wei (魏) as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his personal name, as their surname. (ii) from the personal name Wan (萬), style name of Rui Bo (芮伯, the Earl of Rui), an official of the Western Zhou dynasty (1046–771  BC ), who was granted the fief Rui (located in Ruicheng in Shaanxi province). Some of his descendants inherited Rui (芮), the name of the fief, as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his style name, as their surname. (iii) from the placename Wan (萬), the name of a fief (located in Juxian in Shandong province) granted during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ) to an official in the ancient state of Chu. (iv) from the first element of the name of the Wan Si (萬俟) family, who lived in the downstream areas of the Yellow River during the Northern Qi dynasty (550–577  AD ). (v) from the second element of the name of the Tu Wan (吐萬) family, who are members of the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 完, meaning ‘complete’ in Chinese: (i) said to be borne by the descendants of Huan Zhui, a grandson of the Duke Huan of Song (ruler of the state of Song, died 651  BC ). (ii) from Wan (完), the name of Qu Wan (屈完), an official in the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn Period (770–476  BC ). (iii) shortened form of the compound surname Wan-Yan (完顔), a surname from minority ethnic groups such as Juchen ethnic group in ancient northern China."]}]},{"name":"Heusden","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Ousden (Suffolk) with prosthetic initial <i>H-</i>. The placename derives from Old English <i>ūf</i> ‘owl’ (genitive <i>ūfes</i>) + <i>denu</i> ‘valley’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Jan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jan van Heusden I was born on 30 June 1160, in Heusden, North Brabant, Netherlands, his father, Daniel I van der Merwede, was 35 and his mother, Justine van Heeze-Millen, was 28. He married Aleida Dirk Persijn van Cuijck. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 15 January 1217, in his hometown, at the age of 56."},"et":{"30 June 1160–15 January 1217":"30. juuni 1160–15. jaanuar 1217","1160–1217":"1160–1217","–Female":"Surnud","1195–1242":"1195–1242","1125–1187":"1125–1187","1132–1200":"1132–1200","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","9 September 1195":"9. september 1195","1217":"1217","30 June 1160":"30. juuni 1160","1125":"1125","1200":"1200","15 January 1217":"15. jaanuar 1217","2 februari 1187":"2. veebruar 1187","Heusden, Asten, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Asten, Noord-Brabant, Madalmaad","Heusden, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Noord-Brabant, Madalmaad","Salm, Daun, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Salm, Daun, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"30 June 1160–15 January 1217":"30. kesäkuuta 1160–15. tammikuuta 1217","1160–1217":"1160–1217","–Female":"Kuollut","1195–1242":"1195–1242","1125–1187":"1125–1187","1132–1200":"1132–1200","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","9 September 1195":"9. syyskuuta 1195","1217":"1217","30 June 1160":"30. kesäkuuta 1160","1125":"1125","1200":"1200","15 January 1217":"15. tammikuuta 1217","2 februari 1187":"2. helmikuuta 1187","Heusden, Asten, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Asten, Noord-Brabant, Alankomaat","Heusden, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Heusden, Noord-Brabant, Alankomaat","Salm, Daun, Rhine